data: {"type":"opportunity","opportunity":{"id":"4dde5ade-347d-4702-85c6-1758e1795f0a","scrapedApp":{"id":"1440975537","title":"Otsimo | Speech Therapy SLP","store":"app_store","genre":"Education","score":3.35196,"ratings":179,"reviewCount":50,"installs":"N/A","description":"From award-winning creators! Otsimo | Speech Therapy SLP is proud to be the only Speech Therapy app that uses voice and speech recognition technology and machine learning; it understands exactly what you are trying to say! \n\nFor those who experience speech related issues such as:\n- Delayed speech (late talkers),\n- Non-verbal autism and down syndrome affecting speech,\n- Difficulty to articulate themselves and enunciate,\n- Apraxia,\n- Aphasia,\n- Stuttering\n- Articulation issues,\nCan use Otsimo | Speech Therapy SLP for speech practice efforts and improving their speech. \n\nThe speech games designed specifically for individuals, are created under the guidance of parents, speech language pathologists (slps), and therapeutic activity experts. The assistive games in Otsimo | Speech Therapy SLP aim to improve speech and communication skills.\n\nAll the reasons to try out Otsimo | Speech Therapy:\n- We use voice and speech recognition technology to evaluate what is being said for accurate results, enhancing the speech therapy experience. \n- With receptive, machine learning technology, the app detects whether or not the articulation and pronunciation is being improved.\n- Each speech exercise is followed by funny filters, with hats and masks as rewards, to make learning more fun.\n- Each speech exercise also has 200+ stickers to be collected, encouraging the individual to be more engaged with the speech therapy.\n- The exercises involve repetition, a popular method of aba speech therapy, which helps with the development of the person with speech impediments.\n- As part of certified professional therapy, we use video modelling that enables learning from peers through mimicking.\n- Our apps are updated on a weekly basis with exciting content and speech activities, so you never get bored of learning new words.\n- Otsimo | Speech Therapy also offers settings for parental control.\n\n For purposes of learning and development, Otsimo | Speech Therapy SLP will teach how to articulate the correct sound of vowels and consonants and more, so they can learn to communicate orally in an improved way.\n\nOtsimo | Speech Therapy SLP is a pocket SLP that you can use as speech therapy at home. Awarded as the best therapy activities app, it aims to reduce any kind of language and speech problems, in a fun way!\n\nThe Otsimo | Speech Therapy app consists of 15+ categories, including First Words, Basic Shapes, Body Parts, Safari Club, Tongue Acrobatics, Rainbow Splash! Each category is designed to stimulate sound production.\n\nOtsimo | Speech Therapy SLP journey starts with 7-days free trial or monthly subscription. We offer monthly, annual and lifetime subscriptions. Actual charges might be converted to local currency depending on your country of residence. At the confirmation of purchase, payment will be charged to your Apple ID account. \n\nSubscriptions automatically renew unless auto-renew is turned off at least 24-hours before the end of the current subscription period. Our account will be charged for renewal within 24-hours prior to the end of the current period, and the cost of the renewal will be identified. Subscriptions may be managed by the user. Auto-renewal may be turned off by going to the user’s Account Settings after purchase. Any unused portion of a free trial period, if offered, will be forfeited when the user purchases a subscription to the app. \n\nDisclaimer: Otsimo | Speech Therapy SLP is developed in a way that can be used with a guardian. Any individual can benefit from the service without any age restriction. \n\nFor more information: \nPrivacy Policy & Terms of Use - https://otsimo.com/en/legal/privacy-speech/\nPayment Policy - https://otsimo.com/legal/payment.html","icon":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Purple221/v4/31/22/44/3122445d-1bd6-bc0a-a601-c572ec432485/AppIcon-0-0-1x_U007emarketing-0-8-0-85-220.png/512x512bb.jpg","url":"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/otsimo-speech-therapy-slp/id1440975537?uo=4","developer":"Otsimo","isEstimatedInstalls":false,"price":0,"free":true,"histogram":{"1":57,"2":10,"3":11,"4":15,"5":86}},"reviews":[{"id":"12988904180","text":"Throws out of the app. This app always throws us out. Kids have to login again and again.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"12684221384","text":"Not working. It's opening and working but when I tap on an exercise and it's about to start, it restarts again.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"11112378392","text":"My kid love it 🤍🤍🤍. Me and my kid love Otsimo Speech Therapy. My kid is 4 and it helps him lots. The games is real fun and he be learning new words all the time. I seen a big difference since he start using it. Easy to use too!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"11047550580","text":"Rip off. I had paid for the app, and it also had pulled from my Apple Pay but it keeps showing that I don’t have a subscription and that I need to pay for it when I’ve put money into this.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"11043541645","text":"Not a Free App. After downloading, sharing information about my child, and creating a login, I discovered that this app wanted to charge a monthly fee. It also indicated that I could have a 1 week free trial, but wouldn’t go past that screen.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"10947042564","text":"Best app for speech delay !! Give it a try !. I swear this is  the best app you can find  for kids who have delays in speech !  i tried so many apps for my toddler ( alomost 3 yrs old ) who has speech delay nothing helped her !!! I downloaded otsimo speech app and in just two weeks my daughter started to say a lot of words  !!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"10664078395","text":"Totally worthless. SCAM. My daughter loved this app & since she’s 3.5 years old but still has a lot of trouble forming words (only able to say maybe 5 words clearly/that other people can understand) - despite understanding at least 90% of the English language, I purchased an annual subscription without hesitation. I regret that decision greatly, as now we cannot afford another app.\n\nShe did great with Otsimo at first & even started speaking a lot more clearly. But that didn’t last, as we had a lot of issues that I initially thought was caused by the audio from the children speaking within the app - so I purchased her a headset. That did nothing & she soon reverted back to the way she spoke before. After that, I realized even when she didn’t make a single sound in a quiet room, the app would pass her & she’d be taken to the next level.\n\nI’ve never been so infuriated with an app & feel extremely cheated. Its unbelievably cruel & disgusting that a company would take advantage of children with speech delay and/or special needs. It makes me sick.\n\nI unsubscribed to Otsimo & at the end of the year I plan to use Homer for educational support. However to parents looking for a cheaper alternative to apps aimed directly at speech therapy:\nWe just discovered “Paw Patrol Academy” which has some pretty cool games directed towards letters & their sounds. Since pretty much every toddler these days is obsessed with Paw Patrol, I’d say that’s one which is definitely worthy of a subscription, even if it doesn’t work out specifically for speech related issues.\n\n[Our story]\nMy daughter’s issues stem from/started with extremely low confidence due to emotional abuse from her father, which then forced us to bounce from home to home and now we are stuck in limbo as we wait for our forever-home to be built. She gave up on everything, and is now severely behind on everything too. She even had to get 90% of her teeth capped because of the damage her father did (which screwed up her confidence even more, as well as making it harder for her to speak clearly)… no child deserves a mouth full of silver teeth.\nWhere we live, the wait time to see any pediatric therapist is 17 months - not even taking into account the wait time to see a therapist within a more specialized field such as speech pathology. So… there’s no choice but to use whatever resources we have at our disposal.\n\nSo with that said, it makes me even more sick for an app like this to scam innocents. My little girl has been through enough suffering. Shame on you for making life even harder for my sweet girl - who goes above & beyond to make every single person around her happy (both loved ones & total strangers).\n\nPlease do NOT purchase a subscription to this app. If you are still determined to do so after reading this review (and the other negative reviews which I somehow missed), try a monthly subscription first - NOT annual. I wish I hadn’t been so hasty to spend +$50 on this app, but I got so excited when she showed such interest in it & I genuinely just want what’s best for my little girl - who is literally my entire world and I’d do absolutely anything for (which means I’ll be single the rest of my life and I am totally content with that if it means she is happy, healthy, and never feels less than my everything).\n\nThank you for your time.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"10663648389","text":"Not SLP. This is not a bad app but it’s dishonest marketing. It’s not a replacement for SLP services and could delay parents in seeking out services which means missing valuable time in therapy. It’s not individualized and literally just works on imitation. Working on imitation is great but it does not target play skills, could delay AAC or signs, does not increase functional communication, and does not help articulation.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"10202328863","text":"Not that useful. It’s just a marketing scam. Only a few words have videos, rest, just a kid repeats the word. Not useful at all. And I’m pretty sure I singed up for monthly but it charged me yearly subscription","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"9069499089","text":"Transaction system bug. I downloaded this app for a annual membership which provide 7 days free trial. I tried this app and it was too simple for my son so I cancelled the subscription right away. It turned out the expiration date will be a year later which means the 7 day free trial didn’t exist. I don’t know if it is a bug but I’m not happy with this!","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"8706775082","text":"Please let me cancel this app. It doesn’t even show me I am subscribed to this app yet I know I am so please how do I cancel it before the subscription is over with? I’ll change my review if you help me","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"8670820404","text":"2 separate apps. I'm already paying for the other app. Why not allow the subscription to be for both. Or just made it be one app all together. People really be out here money hungry and taking advantage of parents trying to help their children.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"8373718165","text":"Does not work on iPad 9. Terrible, needs an update","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"8368145171","text":"Unrealistic. It ask my child to make the F sound yet my child made just random noises and it still rewarded him. What kind of sense does that make? If youre going to teach it, then teach it right.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"8354268286","text":"thanks. I can't leave! Thanks again!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"8342174309","text":"I am a speech therapist. I am a speech therapist and I have been using Otsimo for the past few months. It is a great tool for practicing speech therapy exercises at home with kids. The app is easy to use and has helped my patients improve their articulation skills.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"8340585557","text":"Works good. Works good and support is helpful","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"8316768105","text":"Recommend. This app isn’t just got minors I’m 30 years old and after having 4 strokes before the age 28 this app has helped me relearn how to speak I still struggle with shudder but I am getting there thank to this app","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"7957798300","text":"Glitches. App keeps glitching out to the point where it won’t even finish one clip before the app mysteriously shuts off. So much for helping my child speak.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"7954090592","text":"App Crashing. With every use, the app crashes after interpreting sound. The concept is great, but not if it crashes constantly.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"7796479039","text":"I can’t thank you enough. My son has 2nd level autism, and he HAD speech delay. Why I am writing HAD, because he had it until I found this incredible application. My husband, me, his speech therapist - everybody was trying to make him to say at least mom and dad, but no success. When I downloaded this app I thought at least he will play games. After ONE WEEK I saw how my son is imitating lip movements of the kids from the screen, but still no sound and it already was a miracle for us at least he tries to imitate. After 2 WEEKS he said his first words MOM,MOM,MOM, then DAD,DAD,DAD. OMG my husband And I were in tears. Because psychologist said he may never speAk, and now after 6 months he is putting 2-3 words together, sometimes making short sentences. For someone else it may seem pretty normal for a kid at his 32 months to say these words, but for a mom with a kid with autism its a miracle. Thank you so much for this application.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"7560882350","text":"My 3 1/2 year old was not interested. I was extremely excited to download this app since I saw so many good reviews. The first day we opened the app he was happy to see himself and giggled. Then the kids repeating the words scared him and he ran away screaming. We tried a few times and he definitely didn’t enjoy it. The kids voices weren’t very clear and even if you turn down the volume it was still not very clear. \nI cancelled the subscription I hope I’m not charged for the full year I don’t think we had it installed for more than a week.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"7549244577","text":"Keeps crashing!!. I would love to try the app and help my kids who are 2 and 1 and after reading reviews I thought this would be the perfect way to do so but as soon as I purchased the pro account the app won’t stop crashing! It took me multiple reloads to just get the kids accounts set up. Highly disappointed","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"7461648125","text":"Wants paid subscription. App requires a paid subscription","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"7409633654","text":"It’s good. Still crashes.. It’s a great app. It’s a shame it crashes every ten minutes and seems to loose all progress.\n\nAlso, if my son says any sound, it counts it towards the word he’s learning. So if he says “dad” instead of “mom” it still says it counts. \n\nA few bugs need working out. Overall, not a bad app.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"7148682318","text":"Malfunction. After every 2 minutes in the app the words the kids are saying become significantly distorted and the only fix is to completely restart the app. Very frustrating.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"7074083130","text":"Took my money before free trail. I decided to try out the free trial but it took out $58 from my account right away.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"7061869185","text":"Not worth it. Tried the app and it doesnt work well with the ipad. The kids have that are used on the app either speak too fast or have some type of speech impediment which is ridiculous for a speech therapy app. We used it for a month and i feel like i wasted my money.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"6836224679","text":"Disappointed. Why do the matching games use identical images 90% of the time?  Even in hard mode!  Love the matching of two similar images that represent a given concept, but matching identical images is a different and much simpler learning goal.  It’s a good challenge for a 1 yr old or chimpanzee in the lab, but I was hoping to see more matching of non-identical images.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"6827201732","text":"Please fix filters for selfies. This app is pretty good for all the foundations of speech such as learning mouth movements. My main complaint though is that the filters for taking pictures end up turning upside down each time so I am constantly trying to turn the iPad different ways for my toddler. The little selfies are a big motivator so I wish that part would work better.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"6597370384","text":"Low quality engagement, not motivating for my son.. Not sure why this app has high reviews.  We tried it all day with my 2.5 yr old autistic son. He was not engaging with the content, presented activities didn’t really motivate participation, and overall I don’t think it is worth any payments required post trial.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"6593255543","text":"Fishy!. Everything loads well except when you need the to adjust your subscription. It feels like a trap because I’ve been unable to access it. It’s been loading ever since...","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"6583538892","text":"Too expensive. I would love to give a better star review, but just to try it there’s only 3 words, that most babies already know how to say. To get anymore, there’s a 70% off sale for $4.50 per month. That’s just horrible. How will I even know if it helps, if there’s only 3 words, Mommy, baby, and I forget the 3rd that are free. \nDon’t waste you time or storage space on this app, unless you’re will to put money out for it.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"6578507456","text":"Disappointed. We wasted our money. Most of the children in the software weren’t happy about their words. My son don’t t want to repeat because they are grumpy. The worst is the system recognizes every whispers like even my son makes 'umm' sounds.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"6464051401","text":"It’s not great. My son didn't engage with the app. It was just drills of words. I wish the audio was better and I would've liked to see more diversity in the actors. One of the actors seemed to have speech difficulties himself and I am not really enthused about getting my son to mimic him. Unfortunately, I would not recommend.\nIn contrast to another app, this app did excel in a feature where it gave the user a path to learning words.\nNote* I did not use the app beyond the free trial. Your results may vary.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"6459902598","text":"Dice que está en español, pero no. Adquirí la suscripción pensando que estaba en español, pero es falso. Publicidad engañosa","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"6399782874","text":"Same app. I’m not sure why I pay $100+ for Otsimo that I would have to pay extra for essentially the same app","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"6320018345","text":"Subscription based.. Not sure why the app says in store purchases leading people to believe that you can use the app at no cost. And like many apps for the better services or more advanced you can buy extras in the App Store. I hate that. Seems misleading. Just say subscription based right from the purchase information. A lot of apps like this. Very misleading.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"6185647748","text":"Garbage. I tried this on the seven day free trial - which you can only get if at the end the can charge you over $50, get cant trial if you intend to roll into monthly, which is sketchy to begin. The kids - who others have noted have pretty heavy accents - just repeat the words, and it is like the app is hearing the kids say the words and so tells my kid good job whether she said anything at all. Haven’t tried the app “Speech Blubs” yet, because I tried this one first because it was cheaper. Seems like this may be a cheap (well, cheaper, because it’s certainly not cheap!) knockoff of that app.\n\nLong story short, don’t waste your time or money.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"6177202518","text":"A joke.. Decided to give this app a try to assist with my 5 year olds speech. Ten minutes in I hear him saying thirsty as tirsy......turns out it was not him, it was the child in the app. How is this supposed to help a child pronounce words correctly if the children recorded in the app are not even saying it correctly?","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"6059893923","text":"No help. The app is stuck on one activity which has cause a major melt down with my son. He cannnot move on to different activities and it is playing the same video over and over again. I can’t even access the main menu. After paying $50 I am extremely disappointed.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"5956165845","text":"My child and I love the app BUT. For some reason we paid for the monthly subscription and no free trial . And every time we click an animal it won’t let us continue it takes us to the subscription page . Like we did this so many times . We even upgraded our subscription thinking that was the problem. But no :( wish it worked","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"5937279767","text":"Bug needs fixed. I bought the premium today and everything is still locked, it takes me buy the subscription and then says I already bought it.  My son was really excited to use this","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"5933292493","text":"Can’t Understand - heavy accents. This is a great idea, but the kids featured on the video had very heavy accents. This made my son pronounce things with what I can only describe as a Spanish or Brazilian accent. Huge waste of money. It was really expensive to just make my child regress ☹️.  I went with Dotcomtherapy instead and it’s been a god send.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"5926204670","text":"Terrible. There’s no way to see if it is right for my daughter because it forces you to make a payment first.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"5832379377","text":"Doesn’t work. It keeps crashing!","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"5827104955","text":"Login access. I try to get the account info and my code say wrong even though I know it’s right.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"5818420544","text":"Help with subscription. Hi. I can’t figure out how to cancel. This doesn’t suit my needs right now. Can you please assist. Thanks.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"5666425541","text":"Help?. This sounds like an amazing app for my kiddo and his struggles with speech but once I downloaded I am unable to get past a mostly white screen. I cannot even get to the subscribe page to get started.  Am I the only one experiencing this?","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"5546144104","text":"It seems great. Didn’t have it long cause it kept crashing on us","score":3,"date":""}],"sentiment":{"overallSentiment":"negative","painPoints":[{"issue":"App crashes and forces repeated logins","frequency":"high","severity":"critical","sampleQuotes":["Throws out of the app. This app always throws us out. Kids have to login again and again.","It's opening and working but when I tap on an exercise and it's about to start, it restarts again."]},{"issue":"Billing and subscription issues","frequency":"high","severity":"critical","sampleQuotes":["I had paid for the app, and it also had pulled from my Apple Pay but it keeps showing that I don't have a subscription and that I need to pay for it when I've put money into this.","I tried this app and it was too simple for my son so I cancelled the subscription right away. It turned out the expiration date will be a year later which means the 7 day free trial didn't exist."]},{"issue":"Misleading marketing and false effectiveness claims","frequency":"high","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["Its unbelievably cruel & disgusting that a company would take advantage of children with speech delay and/or special needs.","This is not a bad app but it's dishonest marketing. It's not a replacement for SLP services and could delay parents in seeking out services which means missing valuable time in therapy."]},{"issue":"Inadequate speech therapy methodology","frequency":"medium","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["Even when she didn't make a single sound in a quiet room, the app would pass her & she'd be taken to the next level.","It does not target play skills, could delay AAC or signs, does not increase functional communication, and does not help articulation."]},{"issue":"Limited content and repetitive exercises","frequency":"medium","severity":"minor","sampleQuotes":["Only a few words have videos, rest, just a kid repeats the word. Not useful at all.","It's just a marketing scam with no real value."]}],"featureRequests":[{"feature":"More comprehensive speech therapy content with video demonstrations","demand":"high","sampleQuotes":["Only a few words have videos, rest, just a kid repeats the word.","The games should be more interactive and provide better feedback on pronunciation."]},{"feature":"Improved app stability and bug fixes","demand":"high","sampleQuotes":["This app always throws us out.","The app restarts when you try to start an exercise."]},{"feature":"Transparent and honest billing practices","demand":"high","sampleQuotes":["There should be a clear free trial period without automatic charges.","Need to show what subscription plan users are actually on."]}],"praisedAspects":["Engaging and fun games that children enjoy","Effective for improving word repetition and vocabulary","Easy to use interface","Some users reported improvement in speech clarity"],"summary":"Otsimo | Speech Therapy SLP has overwhelmingly negative sentiment driven by critical billing fraud, app crashes, and misleading marketing claims. While some users initially praised its engaging games and reported speech improvements, the majority felt cheated by deceptive subscription practices, inadequate therapeutic methodology, and unreliable app performance. Users criticize the app for masquerading as a professional speech-language pathology tool when it primarily focuses on simple word repetition, potentially delaying parents from seeking legitimate therapy services."},"score":{"marketSize":14,"dissatisfaction":41,"feasibility":35,"compositeScore":31},"scanId":"fceeb718-5c98-4761-b59a-4f7d7f1fc08b","createdAt":"2026-03-08T15:47:01.749Z","gapAnalysis":null,"blueOcean":null}}

data: {"type":"opportunity","opportunity":{"id":"4f45d382-f88b-47c2-8feb-619d51160bb4","scrapedApp":{"id":"1535324205","title":"Vocal Image: AI Speaking Coach","store":"app_store","genre":"Education","score":4.5294,"ratings":9,"reviewCount":50,"installs":"N/A","description":"Vocal Image — your personal AI communication coach! Transform your voice and interpersonal skills through engaging, bite-sized training sessions that seamlessly integrate into your busy lifestyle.\n\nWhether you're preparing for a job interview, giving a presentation, or simply wanting to sound more confident in daily conversations, Vocal Image helps you speak with clarity and impact in any situation.\n\n————————\nWHAT CAN VOCAL IMAGE HELP YOU WITH?\n\n* Professional Communication\nMaster verbal techniques, communication styles, and strategies that elevate your professional presence.\n\n* Public Speaking & Presentations\nDevelop a commanding vocal presence for meetings, talks, and on-stage moments.\n\n* Interview Confidence\nImprove articulation, tone, and pacing to make a strong impression under pressure.\n\n* Voice Quality Enhancement\nStrengthen your speaking voice with targeted, healthy vocal exercises.\n\n* Accent & Pronunciation\nRefine pronunciation and reduce accent barriers to speak more clearly, whatever your accent.\n\n* Social Skills & Confidence\nProject self-assurance and connect more effectively in everyday conversations.\n\n* Interpersonal Communication\nUse tone, pacing, and expression to communicate with clarity and empathy.\n\n————————\nHOW VOCAL IMAGE WORKS\n\n* AI Voice Evaluation\nAnalyze your voice to identify strengths and opportunities, then get personalized recommendations.\n\n* Expert Video Coaching\nPractice alongside professional coaches in interactive sessions focused on real-world improvement.\n\n* Personalized Training Plan\nFollow a plan tailored to your goals, schedule, and current ability.\n\n* Tongue Twister Drills (Articulation Training)\nListen to professionally recorded tongue twisters, then record your take. Receive instant Clarity and Speed scores and watch them improve over time.\n\n* Daily Radio-Style Lessons\nShort, daily audio episodes with evidence-based tips you can apply immediately to speak better—fast.\n\n* Daily Practice Routine\nStay consistent with quick sessions that fit your day, plus streaks and progress tracking.\n\n* Community Feedback\nJoin 4,000,000+ users and receive constructive feedback on your progress.\n\n————————\nSUBSCRIPTION TERMS\n\nAfter you download the app, you can start a free trial.\n\nUnless you cancel at least 24 hours before the end of the free trial, you’ll be automatically charged the price shown on the payment screen for your chosen subscription period. We’ll send a reminder before your trial ends.\n\nSubscriptions renew automatically at the end of each period (weekly, monthly, every 3 months, yearly, or as selected) until you cancel. Canceling stops future renewals; you’ll retain access to all features for the remainder of your current period.\n\nTerms of Service: https://www.vocalimage.app/terms\nPrivacy Policy: https://www.vocalimage.app/privacy\nQuestions? Contact us: support@vocalimage.app\n\nFollow us:\nYouTube: https://www.youtube.com/@Vocal_Image\nTelegram: https://t.me/vocalimage\nInstagram: https://instagram.com/vocalimage.app\nTikTiok: https://www.tiktok.com/@vocalimage","icon":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Purple221/v4/c9/bd/7d/c9bd7d80-17d8-4e0f-d3b1-da47567d3061/AppIcon-0-0-1x_U007emarketing-0-8-0-85-220.png/512x512bb.jpg","url":"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/vocal-image-ai-speaking-coach/id1535324205?uo=4","developer":"Vocal Image OU","isEstimatedInstalls":false,"price":0,"free":true,"histogram":{"1":549,"2":174,"3":432,"4":764,"5":7316}},"reviews":[{"id":"13818281597","text":"Surprisingly useful. Expected another generic AI app, but 3rd day so far and each day I’ve found challenging in ways I didn’t expect","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13817825025","text":"Ripoff. This app is a total rip off. They take your money and provide nothing in return. Avoid at all costs.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13812614460","text":"Scam. Not helpful at all. Takes money without offering anything in return","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13803554596","text":"All reviews fake. This is complete garbage. Nothing like the presentation on TikTok. A few tongue twisters and a voice recorder that works 10% of the time. Don’t waste your money","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13799060022","text":"Feeling scammed. I’m pretty sure I never subscribed, yet I was suddenly charged $60 on my credit card. That’s extremely shady.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13794593449","text":"scam. not what is advertised - the only reason this app exists is to scam you to pay only to to udersand it is just a scam with no real value","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13783584750","text":"Update after 100days. Editing me review after I’ve been using it for over 100 days straight. Still too early for me to decide whether a lower rating is due.\n\nSo far it doesn’t appear there was an improvement, according to the confidence scale of their AI model.\n\nAt some point the communication tip keeps on repeating, and are not at all like the Instagram ads (with the phrases suggestions). \n\n\nThe model seems to be inaccurate, especially during the tongue twisters. When I’m doing something wrong, I have no idea and no matter what I do I’m unable to improve the score I get. There are no suggestions either.\n\nFinally, the time it takes to load is just absurd. I had to skip the lesson several times because I just didn’t have time to wait.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13772092558","text":"I am learning a lot about myself through this app. Hi there, my name is Laura! I have been trying to expand my vocabulary for a while now but I didn’t know how! Thanks to this app I am now on my way to not only learning  more about myself, but to learn how people understand me. I am not a native English speaker. I am a native Spanish and French speaker. I started to speak English when I was 10 years old. Now I want the same app but for different languages.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13761007717","text":"Scam. I subscribed on Tiktok for $5 then download the app. The app asked me to subscribe for more money. Impossible to cancel or erase the account. Still the app tries to take more money on my card. Bye","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13757468478","text":"It’s a scam app be careful. Once you get the free trail, on the app there’s no option to cancel the subscription and even it shows there’s no subscription but still they charge you.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13754297376","text":"Be aware of unexpected charges and storage of credit card information. I was brought to this app from Facebook. When paid on their website they did not mention at all automatic renew. I found out about the $9.99 charge later and there is no where from the app nor website to delete my credit card info.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13753635140","text":"Took my money. I wished I had listed to some of the reviews mentioning how they were inappropriately charged.  I signed up for the 7 day free trial. The app specifically tells you that you will be warned two days prior to being charged for the annual subscription of almost 90 dollars.   Well I was never warned and forgot to cancel.  Nevertheless I was charged $90 for an app I don’t need and didn’t like.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13750172281","text":"Charged weekly for $9.99. Initially thought this is a monthly subscription","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13742070343","text":"Tongue twisters and recordings need improvement. For the tongue twisters, all it does is tell me what I did wrong but doesn’t actually tell me how to fix it. I listen to the recording and feel like I am in fact saying it correctly, but then it says I’m not and won’t give any actual feedback on how to do it right. Same with the recordings, all it does is tell me I’m lo in confidence and high in weakness, but doesn’t actually break down how to fix or improve those. So it’s not actually helpful 🙃","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13737819267","text":"Pretty certain this is a scam. Smoke and mirrors with no real content","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13729824684","text":"Bad. This app did NOT need an AI upgrade. I found it more difficult to use and less useful overall. Please do not use AI products, they are all unethical.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13710121207","text":"Ai that gives instant feedback. I downloaded this app based on the ad where there is a split screen, AI agent on the left, the user on the right. The AI giving feedback to the user, ex: to speak 20% slower, lower your voice, etc. I cannot find this exercise. Where do I find this?","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13704718147","text":"Seré honesto y diré la verdad. Es una gran aplicación y muy útil la descargué por curiosidad y para averiguar qué hace y para que es buena y realmente me encanta.  Es muy útil y te prepara para ser un ser humano más inteligente y próspero “si sabes aprovechar su valor”.    La uso en modo gratis y es suficiente para experimentar pero como me gusta la app pase a modo pro para apoyar esta plataforma y siga existiendo. 🙏🏾💪🏽","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13703252189","text":"Scammers. These people keep charging my bank account every week for no reason.  I never signed up with you.  I’ve just looked at the app and deleted it and now who is this I’m getting charged and now there’s no way for me to even find the existing subscription to cancel.   \nPlease help!","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13699754455","text":"It’s ok. But just ok.. It has some useful tips but a bunch of fluff too— the long intro animations for example quickly go from cute to annoying and tedious.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13694390578","text":"Glitching. The app is currently glitching and lessons will not play.  I love the idea of this but currently not functional","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13687624840","text":"Painfully Inefficient. Spend 80$ for filler cartoons, frustration, and worthless ai analysis. \n\nSerious. Don’t waste your time … because that’s what it’s good at … wasting your precious time.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13673554927","text":"Not what advertise. As I see the publicity - this is not what you are getting - not even close to what they show you on the videos","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13652635327","text":"Don’t Do It. This is a complete waste of money and time. Don’t make the same mistake I did.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13634154586","text":"Distracting quests& bad processing. This app sounds promising, I tried it for an hour and it had me do ridiculous side quests that have nothing to do with singing or improving tone/register. I’m not trying to be a bartender to a frog, if this is already happening during the 3rd challenge I’d hate to see how many more of these “challenges” are just fluff. Finally made it to a practice that seemed legitimate, and the “ai processing” kept failing despite my internet connection being great, so the whole reason to use this app (so processing and assisting) didn’t actually work. Not worth $20 a month","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13632132020","text":"Buyer beware. I signed up for the free trial and was charged. I cancelled the service and have been charged for the months following my cancellation sand no longer have access to the ap. My request to the app’s customer service requesting that they honor the cancellation and stop charging my card went unanswered.  Have now been charged about $100 for an ap I used once and cancelled.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13630005299","text":"Feels like a scam. I signed up for this and paid them $30 but none of the questions I answered have anything to do with the exercises they are giving me.  \n\nI have a nasally voice and a slight lisp and I need help with that but both nothing in the app addresses that.\n\nThe app sucks and I think this is a scam to charge my credit card every month so I deleted my subscription and deleted the no in the app.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13629785667","text":"My card was charged unexpectedly. I bought one year subscription on sale and after 3 months they charged my card $59.99 without a notice or any email confirmations.\n\nFeels like scam","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13627311317","text":"Quotes in the video. It’s a good app in many ways but I wish the quote(s) shown in the start of the video pause and I get the opportunity to read them. It just pass by so fast!","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13627053675","text":"Still, Predatory Subscription Policy. When I started the trial, the app kept saying not to worry about forgetting to cancel, they will send me reminders several times before the subscription starts. I never got any reminders. I tried canceling on the 7th day but it had already charged my credit card. I email the company but did not hear back. It has been three days. \nThe reason why I am canceling is the lessons are simply too long. I don’t have the time to use it and was planning on trying it again when I have more time. Also, it does not go back to the lesson I missed the day before. It just moves on. I found that disappointing. The ai evaluations takes a long time, adding to the amount of time on the app. The daily lessons take a minimum of 30 minutes.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13619481872","text":"Not at all helpful. Needs to state sign up and account with ongoing service fees is mandatory. Not contains in app purchases. As if it was a tool freely offered with premium features that can enhance the tools performance. I don’t want to sign up. I didn’t finish signing up. Don’t charge my account for anything. Predators. 🧿","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13619284859","text":"SCAM. This company is a scam! Please do not give them your credit card information. They have been charging my card daily $10. I didn’t catch it and now disputing with my credit card company and will be reporting to the Better Business Bureau.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13618284494","text":"Doesn’t include Context Lessons. This is great if you want to change the TONE of your voice. But if you want to stop saying umm or huhhh there’s no lesson in here on how to rephrase your thought process so you say better things instead. The IG ad was falsely advertised. Dont waste your time if this was what you wanted to improve on.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13616781811","text":"Me gusta la app pero…. Hay muchas cosas en la App que son de pagar y me gustaría más cosas gratis, entiendo q tiene que ganar dinero pero poniendo todo tan caro y casi nada gratis no lo veo","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13614221563","text":"Not as advertised. I got bamboozled! I took the assessment quiz for this app that I saw on Instagram, and liked what it said it could do for me in terms of improving my speech and communication skills. So I bought the app, but it does absolutely nothing of what the advertisement told me it was going to do. Thank goodness I only paid for the $4.99 package for one week, and not something more expensive.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13602222989","text":"Waste of money. Complete waste of money. I want a refund.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13594827004","text":"A total waste. I bought this from an IG ad as they said it would help develop communication skills. Instead, this app puts you through third-grade level, pointless exercises. Flushed $$ down the toilet on this one.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13588507222","text":"Has potential but not realistic. This app would be more effective if it included real life scenarios, or improv communication. The only practice available is to read excerpts.. reading is not going to improve your public speaking skills. You don’t go out and read a book to someone, you go out and speak to someone. A major flaw. I am disappointed I purchased the full year. After one week, the exercises become repetitive and they are not in tune with real life scenarios. Great for becoming more aware of pitch, volume etc but for anyone with social anxiety, reading is not going to change or improve your communication. You don’t get to read an excerpt in social situations in the real world.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13585996637","text":"Terrible. I want a full refund. I am beyond disappointed in how terrible this app is. I know how to say Crisp. Waste of money.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13585942113","text":"Good but does not work regularly. The app is fantastic but it does get stuck and not be able to use couple of days!","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13571978544","text":"This app sucks. Where’s the language support? This all feels like breathing exercises that go on wayyy too long. This app is a scam from what I’m seeing","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13567472974","text":"Más de lo que esperaba. Esta aplicación me ha sorprendido gratamente. Es muy fluida, cuenta con excelentes animaciones y es muy motivadora.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13563474818","text":"Junk. No initial vocal recordings to identify pitch or confidence. Only self diagnosis questions with a 140$ subscription. Complete trash. Deleted and refunded.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13558298662","text":"Unclear in terms of how you’re supposed to use the app. You have to earn points. It’s unclear regarding how you’re supposed to use the app.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13547958503","text":"OPTIONS. This app gives you options on what you want to do whether it’s something for fun or something for work and I appreciate it","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13538913193","text":"This app sucks you into paying. This is one of those apps that sucks you into paying and then silently keeps charging even if you use them or not. Stay away!","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13536245364","text":"Excellent Customer Service. Customer service is very professional, supportive and helpful!","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13521330891","text":"Fraud scam. They charged $89.99 May2025, this was working on phone in the begining. i am not able to login now. App is not even recognizing my email id & it captured my password. Looks like fraud scam. Apple please investigate.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13518855883","text":"Great app. This is an amazing app but I did not know I was supposed to pay for it after 5 free days.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13511404124","text":"Not helpful for me. I wanted to broaden my vocabulary and sound  more professional and wanted to help with the correct pronunciation but was not helping me. They make you do exercises of breathing and a type of humming but don’t correct you on where you did wrong just shows you were you didn’t sound accurate. \nI paid in advance and I regretted buying it I already delete my account and the app on my phone. They give you tips all of them in writing so you can’t really hear or see how they should sound or how you should correct it they just rate you.","score":1,"date":""}],"sentiment":{"overallSentiment":"negative","painPoints":[{"issue":"Fraudulent billing and unauthorized charges","frequency":"high","severity":"critical","sampleQuotes":["I'm pretty sure I never subscribed, yet I was suddenly charged $60 on my credit card. That's extremely shady.","I subscribed on Tiktok for $5 then download the app. The app asked me to subscribe for more money. Impossible to cancel or erase the account. Still the app tries to take more money on my card."]},{"issue":"No value or meaningful improvement","frequency":"high","severity":"critical","sampleQuotes":["This app is a total rip off. They take your money and provide nothing in return.","So far it doesn't appear there was an improvement, according to the confidence scale of their AI model."]},{"issue":"Inaccurate AI feedback and scoring","frequency":"medium","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["The model seems to be inaccurate, especially during the tongue twisters. When I'm doing something wrong, I have no idea.","There are no suggestions either."]},{"issue":"Slow app performance and loading times","frequency":"medium","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["The time it takes to load is just absurd. I had to skip the lesson several times because I just didn't have time to wait."]},{"issue":"Misleading advertising and false claims","frequency":"high","severity":"critical","sampleQuotes":["This is complete garbage. Nothing like the presentation on TikTok.","All reviews fake."]},{"issue":"Inability to cancel subscription","frequency":"medium","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["Once you get the free trail, on the app there's no option to cancel the subscription.","Impossible to cancel or erase the account."]}],"featureRequests":[{"feature":"Multilingual versions of the app","demand":"low","sampleQuotes":["I want the same app but for different languages."]},{"feature":"Accurate AI feedback with personalized suggestions","demand":"high","sampleQuotes":["Need real-time suggestions for improvement during exercises.","The AI should provide specific guidance on what's wrong and how to fix it."]},{"feature":"Improved app loading speed and performance","demand":"high","sampleQuotes":["The time it takes to load is just absurd."]},{"feature":"Easy and transparent subscription cancellation","demand":"high","sampleQuotes":["There's no option to cancel the subscription.","Make it simple to manage account and billing."]}],"praisedAspects":["Provides interesting self-awareness insights about speaking patterns","Helps with vocabulary expansion for non-native speakers","Well-designed exercises when they work properly"],"summary":"Vocal Image: AI Speaking Coach has strongly negative sentiment characterized by widespread fraud allegations, unauthorized charges, and lack of tangible improvement. The primary complaint is deceptive billing practices with difficult or impossible cancellation options. Users report the AI feedback is inaccurate, app performance is poor, and the actual content bears little resemblance to TikTok marketing claims. While a small minority found some value in self-reflection aspects, the overwhelming sentiment indicates this is perceived as a pay-to-scam application rather than a legitimate speaking coach tool."},"score":{"marketSize":14,"dissatisfaction":12,"feasibility":72,"compositeScore":31},"scanId":"fceeb718-5c98-4761-b59a-4f7d7f1fc08b","createdAt":"2026-03-08T15:47:02.125Z","gapAnalysis":null,"blueOcean":null}}

