data: {"type":"opportunity","opportunity":{"id":"277ec974-ea52-4b8c-962c-a1439a797432","scrapedApp":{"id":"829587759","title":"Babbel - Language Learning","store":"app_store","genre":"6017","score":0,"ratings":0,"reviewCount":50,"installs":"N/A","description":"Speak a new language with confidence – get Babbel, the award-winning app built by 200+ language experts and trusted by millions worldwide.\n\nLearn a new language faster with bite-sized lessons designed to fit your everyday life. With Babbel’s proven method, you could start having real conversations in as little as 3 weeks. Your language learning adventure starts with a lesson.\n\nWHY BABBEL WORKS\n• Research-proven results Efficacy backed by researchers at Yale University: 100% improved their oral proficiency in 3 months.*\n\n• Expert-built courses Courses are created by language experts and tailored to your native language, so you learn naturally and efficiently.\n\n• Speak with confidence Improve your pronunciation and rehearse out loud with interactive conversation practice.\n\nTRUSTED BY MILLIONS\n• 25 million subscriptions sold \n• 1.5 million 5-star ratings (based on App store ratings) \n• After 10 hours with Babbel, 96% of learners saw better test scores on grammar and vocabulary**\n\nBUILT FOR REAL LIFE\n• Short, effective lessons: Learn in as little as 10 minutes a day \n• Lessons for every motivation: Learn for travel, work, or fun \n• Listen, speak, write: Options for every learning style \n• Stress-free conversation practice: Build confidence with Guided Conversations, then practice freely with Babbel Speak (Beta) \n• Smart review system: Boosts learning and retention \n• Grammar in context: Clear explanations exactly when you need them \n• Offline mode: Download lessons and learn anywhere, anytime \n• 5,000+ courses: Over 60,000 lessons across all languages\n\nLEARN 14 LANGUAGES\nSpanish (Latin American or Spain), French, Italian, German, Portuguese, English (American or British), Russian, Polish, Turkish, Norwegian, Danish, Swedish, Dutch, and Indonesian.\n\nTRY BABBEL TODAY\nDownload Babbel now and take a free lesson.\n\nSUBSCRIPTION DETAILS\nA subscription is required to access full courses for one language. Subscriptions renew automatically unless canceled at least 24 hours before the end of the current period. Payment will be charged to your Apple account.\n\nAvailable plans: \n• 1 month \n• 3 months \n• 6 months \n• 12 months\n\nPrivacy policy: https://about.babbel.com/en/privacy/ Terms of use: https://about.babbel.com/en/terms/\n\nLEARN MORE\nRead Babbel Magazine for tips and insights: https://www.babbel.com/en/magazine\n\nFollow us: Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/babbelusa Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/Babbel.usa\n\nCONTACT US\nQuestions or feedback? Email: support-mobile@babbel.com\n\n*Based on a study conducted with Babbel users learning Spanish. Available at http://bit.ly/BabbelYale. \n**Based on a study conducted with Babbel users learning Spanish. Available: http://bit.ly/BabbelMSU.","icon":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Purple211/v4/62/9a/90/629a904c-b885-f25c-efdc-c44f12716902/AppIcon-Default-0-0-1x_U007epad-0-1-0-0-85-220.png/100x100bb.png","url":"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/babbel-language-learning/id829587759?uo=2","developer":"Babbel GmbH","isEstimatedInstalls":false},"reviews":[{"id":"13820989092","text":"HARD Paywall. There is not a free version of the app. Once you finish the first course, you can’t go further unless you pay for a subscription.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13819868378","text":"Better than the rest. I’ve tried the other apps to learn Spanish and I found this one would be the best. It is a subscription every month or whatever but I found it to be better. I think the other ones have an AI learning model that you’ll probably have to pay for anyway, with this one it’s actually included.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13818069429","text":"Make it free. So I do all of this singing up stuff just to find out you need to pay to unlock all of the courses could of at least told me before it cost money. Duolingo’s better","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13818052400","text":"Has a few quirks. But all around a great learning tool. Still wish they’d abandoned the streak mechanism bc that leads to a greater tendency to rush thru lessons to keep your streak intact rather than to actually learn, but still way less gamified and way better language exposure than its competitor.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13818017546","text":"Very good. It could be a little las pricey but thats the only problem","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13817056359","text":"Options. I would like a setting that will exclude the LGBTQ lifestyle from the curriculum.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13816890133","text":"not want i need. not helpful when it starts with relationships, not helpful for a work environment","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13813949902","text":"This sucked. I just wanted to learn how to speak Korean or Thai but they barely had any Asian languages at all so I couldn’t even use the app!? 😠","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13813208823","text":"Babbel Swedish. Hearing native speakers is a big plus","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13813154673","text":"Fast, easy. A little too fast, wondering how I will obtain.","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13810643685","text":"Lifetime is worth it!. I love Babbel for language learning, I bought the life time subscription so that I can access all available languages and can come back whenever needed. I just hope they add more languages. Japanese preferred.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13809848070","text":"Babbel App. There are better apps","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13807905258","text":"Practice is limited. Overall, it’s a great app and I am definitely learning. I am frustrated by the app limiting when you can practice. You should be able to practice whenever you want.","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13807531780","text":"Don’t know what happened. I have been using this app since Christmas. I would have given it 4 or 5 stars. I am halfway through A1 and learning a lot. Very pleased. However last night the app changed. While my progress tab shows what I’ve been doing, now the main page shows me back at A1, lesson 1. Even after I found where I should be, now what was 4 learning lessons inside a particular topic, is now just one lesson. Per topic. I am NOT pleased. There’s no way the topics will be covered as well as they were before or practiced as much. I’m totally disappointed in this change.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13806069668","text":"Disappointed. Would like this to partly be on automatic play and repeat. So it is hands free. It is disappointing that it is not.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13805459105","text":"Podcasts. Listening to the podcasts are difficult they have a transcript but no translation \nWhat?? Come on how do we know what they’re saying","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13804310430","text":"Great app. I can’t wait to learn Spanish to go on a mission trip to the Dominican Republic","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13803357095","text":"Babble Review. Super fun and easy to stay interactive with it.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13801845546","text":"I’m forced to :(. My dad forces me to do this every day cuz it’s 100€","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13797030277","text":"Makes you pay. Honestly had high expectations for this one bc I heard a lot of good things about it. But you have to pay huge amounts of money to do more than one lesson, and it’s just not worth it. Don’t waste your time.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13796482319","text":"can only do 1 lesson free 😒. i downloaded the app thinking i would be able to do multiple lessons before needing a subscription till i realized i could only do 1 lesson for free. 🙄","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13795486997","text":"Best language app. I’ve tried them all","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13793747807","text":"🇩🇪. It was kind of boring. It’s always lily You need to change the names.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13793705335","text":"Speaking Help. I really really need this app to have a running list of all vocab I’m introduced to with clickable and searchable lists of pronunciation help.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13793010278","text":"In-depth Learning. This language learning app teaches so much more than just a regular gamified lang learning app. I need an explanation.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13792933322","text":"Learning Spanish. I think the app is good but when the pronouns the Spanish they go entirely to fast and it all gets a bit confusing. Also they take you to the next lesson to fast with really going over the lesson you just completed. There needs to be more repetition.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13789560412","text":"Lessons. The course needs to be more on a beginner’s level where you’re learning words. Then, work into sentences.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13787596506","text":"MONEY BACK GUARANTEE DOES NOT APPLY TO APPLE STORE. you cannot try the app for 20 days and then get your money back as advertised if you purchase through the Apple store.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13786520947","text":"beware of scam charges. if you sign up for a free trial and cancel it, they’ll still charge you for the whole year and deny the refund\n\nanyway the app sucks","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13786102567","text":"The average phrase is far too long and not frequently encountered to gain familiarity.. Many more overlapping and confidence boosting study options are needed. I feel bombarded with 50 different phrases when Im often only marginally comfortable with 20% of the vocabulary and grammar.  Trending downward for this app in the 30-60 day range.","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13785764952","text":"German. The German language of Babbel is well done in how it is presented and formatted for the student to learn.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13784832146","text":"Not free. I don’t understand why the App Store shows and allows apps where it’s show as free with in app purchases, but then after you go through several prompts the only option is to pay to use the app. This is misleading and a waste of time. If you want to charge, fine, but make it obvious upfront.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13784145786","text":"It makes learning easy. I enjoy using this app because it really starts to drill in words and phrases while exposing you to more advanced sentences along the way. The exposure is very helpful and you start to get a feel for the language through the exposure. It's not as animated as some other apps, but it is efficient and it does the job well","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13782823425","text":"Makes learning Spanish easy and fun. Makes learning Spanish easy and fun","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13782692990","text":"Complex grammar. In order to be successful in learning Swedish, a detailed understanding of grammar, verb and noun forms and endings is needed.  Unfortunately, they are introduced with a firehose and not enough opportunity to master them.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13781885838","text":"Best ever. best thing ever ever it’s like messages and speaks and i recommend","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13781303062","text":"Enjoying it. I am enjoying it, even the diversion into dialects. For an English speaker with no genders assigned to most nouns, it would be very helpful if the correct der, die, das Nominative Artikel  would always be included when introducing a German noun.\nAlso I would like more podcast stories to which to listen, and also about other places than Berlin.","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13781055995","text":"It was fun while it lasted. It was a good way to learn Italian but it was really hard to cancel the subscription. I had to delete my whole profile.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13780472640","text":"Get a It Wrong 99% of the Time. I purchased the subscription and it was okay, but once I purchased the “Lifetime” version, it constantly says I’m getting the pronunciations wrong. Like 9 out of 10 attempts. Seriously. The same words and phrases I have been getting correct the entire time. Ridiculous!","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13779689915","text":"Don’t get... I got the app wanting to learn a new language. I signed up, and it seemed promising. As soon as I finished my first lesson which lasted about 10 seconds, it wouldn’t let me touch anything else unless I agreed to a $110 dollar subscription plan.. Do not get, it’s a scam!!","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13779475091","text":"AI for speaking practice 👎🏽. I like the listening lessons but am very disappointed that the speaking lessons use AI. I wish you could practice speaking without using AI. I wish I knew that before paying for the app. Would not have subscribed if I knew AI was being used to support speaking practice.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13779234424","text":"Come on now. You could at least use the word of the not everyday in the sentence, but you chose to use a kind of word like it! I put Latin American and now I get more European words!😡A year and I still can’t say on on the left next to the bano Still not giving me hints for words that are not the lauguage im trying to learn! Now this thing won’t stick to one word, it keeps me confused by using words I’ve never heard of for thing I’m still learning what they are in Mexican, not European versions!I did go on the app yesterday only a few minutes but it did say I got a new day! This makes me not want to bother with it anymore","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13778651994","text":"Enjoying my Babbel time. I’m starting see some progress in my Spanish understanding. Once I take time to start my lessons, I find them very rewarding.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13777288712","text":"Laima. I like to start on a higher lever. I reached a score of 45 at duo lingo","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13775547241","text":"Great app on iPad. Please allow split screen on this though.  So we can use a secondary source","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13775281424","text":"Not getting it. Not getting the conjugations, need them more all at once","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13774177154","text":"Bait and switch. I like the language learning method, but two months into my subscription I was prompted to share my voice data for training. When I declined, the speaking exercises were all disabled. Not OK!","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13774094888","text":"The consonants sound the same. I did a lesson learning how to pronounce BTDGP and the pronunciation of B D P & T sounded exactly the same from the recorded voice. It really was a time waster.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13770886716","text":"Where is an explanation or help?. I found duolingo much easier to learn from.  Anytime I had a question it by was easy to get an answer with a single click. With Babbel I have to use a separate Spanish dictionary or begin a chat with Babbel.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13770711521","text":"Needs more Languages. Great app for teaching what it does have to offer. It doesn't have many Asian languages though and I am specifically looking to learn tagalog.","score":4,"date":""}],"sentiment":{"overallSentiment":"mixed","painPoints":[{"issue":"Aggressive paywall and limited free trial - only one lesson free before requiring subscription","frequency":"high","severity":"critical","sampleQuotes":["There is not a free version of the app. Once you finish the first course, you can't go further unless you pay for a subscription.","i downloaded the app thinking i would be able to do multiple lessons before needing a subscription till i realized i could only do 1 lesson for free."]},{"issue":"High subscription costs","frequency":"medium","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["you have to pay huge amounts of money to do more than one lesson, and it's just not worth it.","It could be a little las pricey but thats the only problem"]},{"issue":"Limited language selection, especially Asian languages","frequency":"medium","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["I just wanted to learn how to speak Korean or Thai but they barely had any Asian languages at all so I couldn't even use the app!?","I just hope they add more languages. Japanese preferred."]},{"issue":"Pace is too fast for retention","frequency":"low","severity":"minor","sampleQuotes":["A little too fast, wondering how I will obtain."]},{"issue":"Streak mechanism encourages rushing through lessons rather than genuine learning","frequency":"low","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["I wish they'd abandoned the streak mechanism bc that leads to a greater tendency to rush thru lessons to keep your streak intact rather than to actually learn"]},{"issue":"Recent app update reduced lesson content and practice opportunities","frequency":"low","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["now what was 4 learning lessons inside a particular topic, is now just one lesson. Per topic. I am NOT pleased. There's no way the topics will be covered as well as they were before."]},{"issue":"Limited practice opportunities - practice is gated and not available on demand","frequency":"low","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["I am frustrated by the app limiting when you can practice. You should be able to practice whenever you want."]},{"issue":"Curriculum content doesn't align with user needs (work-focused learning)","frequency":"low","severity":"minor","sampleQuotes":["not helpful when it starts with relationships, not helpful for a work environment"]}],"featureRequests":[{"feature":"Vocabulary glossary with searchable, clickable pronunciation help for all introduced words","demand":"medium","sampleQuotes":["I really really need this app to have a running list of all vocab I'm introduced to with clickable and searchable lists of pronunciation help."]},{"feature":"Hands-free automatic playback and repeat functionality","demand":"low","sampleQuotes":["Would like this to partly be on automatic play and repeat. So it is hands free. It is disappointing that it is not."]},{"feature":"Add more languages, especially Asian languages like Japanese, Korean, and Thai","demand":"high","sampleQuotes":["I just wanted to learn how to speak Korean or Thai but they barely had any Asian languages at all","I just hope they add more languages. Japanese preferred."]},{"feature":"Work-focused curriculum or content modules","demand":"low","sampleQuotes":["not helpful when it starts with relationships, not helpful for a work environment"]}],"praisedAspects":["Best language learning app compared to competitors like Duolingo","High-quality language exposure with less gamification than competitors","Native speaker audio included in lessons","AI learning model is included in subscription rather than requiring separate payment","Interactive and engaging user experience","Effective learning outcomes with clear progress tracking","Lifetime subscription option provides good long-term value"],"summary":"Babbel receives mixed sentiment with strong praise for its language quality, teaching methodology, and value of included AI features compared to competitors, but significant criticism centers on its aggressive monetization model and limited free trial. The paywall is the primary pain point, with users frustrated about only one free lesson before requiring subscription, combined with high subscription costs. Secondary issues include limited language selection (particularly Asian languages) and recent updates that reduced content depth. Users love the superior language exposure and native speaker audio compared to gamified competitors like Duolingo, making it a quality product held back primarily by pricing and freemium strategy concerns."},"score":{"marketSize":14,"dissatisfaction":25,"feasibility":62,"compositeScore":33},"scanId":"fceeb718-5c98-4761-b59a-4f7d7f1fc08b","createdAt":"2026-03-08T15:47:50.684Z","gapAnalysis":null,"blueOcean":null}}

