data: {"type":"opportunity","opportunity":{"id":"516096e0-cd98-47c6-a392-6edaaa6dd931","scrapedApp":{"id":"1116032929","title":"Gibson: Learn to Play Guitar","store":"app_store","genre":"6017","score":0,"ratings":0,"reviewCount":50,"installs":"N/A","description":"The best guitar learning app from Gibson.\nPerfect if you’re looking for a fun guitar practice app that keeps you motivated.\n\nLooking for the best way to learn guitar at home? Start with Gibson’s step-by-step learning path. Whether you’re picking up a guitar for the first time or leveling up your technique, the Gibson App helps you learn faster with interactive fun lessons, real songs, and real-time feedback. Join millions of guitar players learning with the Gibson App. \n\nBuild real skills across all styles — from your first chords to full songs, fingerpicking, and music theory. New songs added weekly.\n\nFEATURED IN TOP MUSIC MEDIA\n\n“The Gibson App is changing the guitar teaching game.” — Rolling Stone\n\n“For those just starting their guitar journey, the Gibson app will be a godsend. The quality of tuition is second to none.” — Guitar World\n\n\"The Best Guitar Learning App\" - Creative Outlet\n\nLEARN GUITAR FASTER WITH REAL-TIME FEEDBACK\n\nThe app listens to your guitar and gives you instant feedback on your playing, helping you improve timing and technique with every session. Guitar lessons, real songs, interactive tabs, tuner, metronome, and real-time feedback — all in one app.\n\n10,000+ LESSONS, EXERCISES & SONGS\n\nExplore a massive library of lessons and songs across multiple genres, including rock, blues, metal, pop, acoustic, and more.\n\nMASTER EVERY GUITAR SKILL\n\nGo beyond basic chords with a curriculum that covers proper finger placement, strumming patterns, lead guitar, fingerpicking, and music theory. Whether you want to read tabs or understand the fretboard, our world-class teachers guide you from beginner to pro across all genres.\n\nSee your guitar skills grow in real-time with detailed tracking across 300+ techniques, chords, and playing styles—turning invisible practice into measurable mastery.\n\nSTEP-BY-STEP LEARNING PATH (BEGINNER TO PRO)\n\nFollow a fun learning journey created by professional guitar teachers. You’ll always know what to practice next, with lessons designed to keep you progressing.\n\nEVERYTHING YOU NEED TO LEARN & PLAY GUITAR\n\n- Guitar tuner \n\n- Metronome\n\n- Tempo control and looping tools\n\n- Training Calendar to build a consistent routine\n\nTURN YOUR IPHONE/IPAD INTO AN AMPLIFIER\n\nExplore guitar sound effects, play along with your favorite music. Practice with an electric or acoustic guitar.\n\nJOIN THE COMMUNITY\n\nConnect with fellow guitar learners, get access to pro-level guidance, tips, and inspiration.\n\nWATCH GIBSON TV\n\nGibson TV is packed with original series on guitars, music, and culture. Watch, and get inspired by legendary players and iconic stories.\n\nNEW TO GUITAR?\n\n- Is the Gibson App good for complete beginners?\nYes. The Gibson App is designed to help complete beginners learn guitar from scratch with step-by-step lessons and a fun learning path.\n\n- Can I learn guitar on my own?\nAbsolutely. The app is built for self-learners and helps you stay consistent with guided lessons and a Training Calendar.\n\n- Does it work with acoustic and electric guitar?\nYes. The Gibson App works with any guitar.\n\n- Does the app teach real songs?\nYes. Learn real songs with interactive tabs and video lessons.\n\n- Why should I choose Gibson app?\nGibson is the best guitar learning app. Ask our users!\n\nHOW THE GIBSON APP WORKS\n\n- The app listens to your guitar and gives you feedback\n\n- Play along with fun lessons and easy-to-follow tablature\n\n- Advance at your own pace through the step-by-step learning\n\nFREE TRIAL\n\nDay 1: Start free trial\nDay 1 - 7: Full access to all lessons, songs, features\nDay 7: Subscription begins unless canceled\nCancel anytime during the free trial, you won’t be charged\n\nABOUT\n\nThe Gibson App is developed by Zoundio, a music-tech company based in Stockholm, Sweden, in collaboration with Gibson.\n\nCONTACT\n\nHave feedback, questions or suggestions? Contact us at app.support@gibson.com \n\nBy downloading this app, you agree to Apple's Terms of Use: https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/dev/stdeula/","icon":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Purple221/v4/dd/5f/91/dd5f9119-733b-101b-1159-da912f7d7a22/AppIcon-1x_U007epad-0-1-0-0-sRGB-85-220-0.png/100x100bb.png","url":"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/gibson-learn-to-play-guitar/id1116032929?uo=2","developer":"Zoundio","isEstimatedInstalls":false},"reviews":[{"id":"13821696513","text":"Most fun guitar app in the store!. Doesn’t get better than this. Rocksmith+ is terrible and other apps are worse. This is the one!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13792054100","text":"Only thing I’d like added. The app is honestly great and the 25$ a month is not a bad price for how much they’re willing to teach you, the only thing I’d like to add is a friends list. I’d like to be able to have friendly competitions with my friends and keep up with each others progress even if we aren’t in the same league. It could also potentially open the door for mobile play sessions amongst players. Otherwise absolutely love the app and plan to continue using it and referring people to it.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13785527534","text":"Love it. It’s teaching me a lot","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13780092081","text":"Fun. But I’m finding out how much I stink! I need more practice.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13771973714","text":"Up charges!. The premium subscription for 19.99 is misleading when you can’t even access the second lesson without being up charged 4.99.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13752252106","text":"I can’t believe I’m supporting an AI teacher. I am a teacher and absolutely believe in the power of a face-to-face in person interaction for feedback and encouragement. And that is absolutely the best format to learn in, but my schedule does not allow me to meet with a in person teacher right now and this app has been great. Gibson really has evaluated a good curriculum for the theory and the steps that a learner needs to go through. I already knew how to play chords and basic drumming patterns, but I wanted to move up in my ability to play licks and melodies. This is really been a great tool.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13749266674","text":"Great overall. Enjoyed it so far , can be repetitive at times but I guess that’s the point","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13746748247","text":"The best guitar app ever. I love this guitar app I tried a few before and did some online lessons but none has brought me as far as Gibson I feel like I’m learning something everyday I’m also the winner of the Flying V Christmas guitar contest so my hard work is pay off thank you Gibson highly recommend this app","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13732224953","text":"Famous songs=all songs. Buyer beware- when they say pay extra for the famous songs what they actually mean is that the lower tier is lessons only. You can’t even play the songs from the lessons outside on the lesson. Nor can you play songs like happy birthday or jingle bells. I just wish I would have known that when I paid for the service. I read a lot of reviews and fine print, then was blindsided when the trial for that part ran out. Otherwise, I would say it’s one of the best ways to learn the guitar on your own. Everything else I have gotten stuck a few chords in, but since this starts with notes it allows you to get familiar with your guitar and work up some callouses before jumping into chords. It makes learning to play a lot of fun.","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13730249506","text":"Try it for a month first. This app seemed promising but after 3 weeks of daily lessons, I’m no better at guitar. I also did not like the “augmented reality” piece, which involves playing out of key notes in the name of an easier learning curve. This app is really well built and functions great! I just did not take to the teaching method. Ultimately, I’m glad I did not buy the annual subscription.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13728289650","text":"Fantastic.  Great Value. I have tried two other competitor’s apps over the years, Fender and True Fire.  After putting the guitar down for a year or two, I’ve been back at with Gibson for a month.  It works for me.  Having the instant feedback has sped up my progress and allows me to see and hear when I’m making a mistake.  For the price of a few in person lessons, this is an absolute bargain.  Highly recommend you use this on an iPad.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13721333006","text":"Depends…. The lessons are good, but the software does have a hard time picking up a few chords, no matter how good or clear or in tune you play them.\n\nLearning the songs? This app could do so much better.  The lessons are walked through slowly and deliberately, but the songs are thrown together, cheaply and fast by only a quick narration at the beginning of most.  Complex chords that aren’t shown anywhere else in the app are thrown in with complex changes that could be described in the lessons, but just aren’t.  If you’re a fan of 70s 80s 90s hard rock, there’s plenty to do.  If you have a preference for late 90s and 2000s and 2010s you’ll find yourself looking elsewhere.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13712691064","text":"Great app, missing some things. I think the app is great, makes it easy to learn chords, gives you backing tracks to help you stay on rhythm. Wonderful for an intermediate/beginner like myself. Only 2 things I think would make it 5 star. I think there should be a “recap” each time you login to practice, it should go over what you learned last time, other thing might roll into the previous thing mentioned is “pop quizzes” and do random tests to help you retain things. Oh and maybe some better AI during the lesson to say, “looks like this string was muted, try this”. Regardless of 1 star or 3 stars on a lesson, you still get a “good job!”","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13690911667","text":"Ok. The picking up of the notes is not that good with a phone. It works sometime and sometimes it doesn’t","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13675143685","text":"Not impressed. New to guitar, starting learning from this app thought it was great. Up until I pushed play and passed a level without even touching the guitar. Was in a completely quiet room and the app was saying I was doing perfect, then too high, too low, missed. Showed I hit 45% accuracy and I didn’t even have my guitar in my hands. Trash","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13675130820","text":"Sometimes you play one chord and that’s all you play that day. This is a great app and it’s been a lot better than any method I’ve used to try to learn guitar, but there are a few problems. For starters, with the free version you can only do four lessons a day and you just fall short of the qualification for starting a streak and getting AI feedback. I’ve kind of just learned to deal with this though. The infuriating part is that sometimes the app will stop me in the middle of a lesson and give me a really bad score. This wouldn’t be too bad if I could reenter the lesson and finish it, but sometimes I’ve literally played one chord and it exits me out of the lesson. If you get this app prepare to either pay for the premium version or be interrupted after half your lessons and sometimes spend days getting nothing out of your practice time.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13668096972","text":"Great way to learn on your own time. I wish they had this when I was a kid. You can take the lessons in your own time when they give you all the tips and tricks you’re looking for repeatedly so you don’t forget.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13663236910","text":"Amazing in so many ways!. I picked the guitar back up after a 20 year break because my daughter wanted to learn how to play. This app is simply amazing! It got back to where I was prior to putting it down then before I knew it I was better than I was years ago. The lessons are easy to navigate. The song library is plentiful but if theory or genres are your thing there is plenty to do. \n\nI wish this technology was around years ago and I might not have put the guitar down. Not only is it filled with lessons, tips, tricks, etc. it turns your iPad or iPhone into an amp. If you are traveling for work or pleasure, plug into your phone. \n\nI look to me a subscriber for years to come! I am looking forward to progressing with the fun tools they provide.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13660399614","text":"Disappointed. Really disappointed with the app, after I renewed my subscription many artists disappeared, Hendrix, nirvana, metalica, Beatles, foo fighters and others.\nThe website still show some artists that doesn’t exist in the library.\nCostumer service doesn’t answer, it’s is a terrible experience.\n100% regret of this anual subscription.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13657212129","text":"Chuck D. As an absolute beginner, I had no idea where to start. I tried several apps before trying the Gibson app.  The Gibson app has been the perfect training device for me, it is set up in a way that challenges me yet allows me to learn at my own pace. The addition of the music with the training exercises make it enjoyable.  I have watched my progression over the last two months and I have made greater gains in that timeframe than all previous attempts to learn the guitar. I highly recommend this to anyone wanting to up their game.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13644544905","text":"Great. Overall a great app, that has helps me build up speed, and clarity. The ranking system is a fun competitive game. It offers knowledge, tips, and tricks on the music you play.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13642361088","text":"Older equipment operator. Working at playing guitar and sounding better all the time to music I want to play","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13638751262","text":"Excellent!!!. Been playing chords for many years but was never able to to get my fingers apart to play solos and that sort of thing. This app has taken my guitar playing to a whole new level. Thanks to the devs!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13618581437","text":"Good for technique, not the songs. I like this app, but it is not very clear at first what counts as a famous song (any song with a picture on the cover instead of an icon). You also can’t find songs you liked from a lesson in the songs tab. I did find the intro courses neat though, with many genres and scales to learn. The app is good at listening for the notes you play too. Overall it was a good app, you just can’t use the songs tab if you don’t upgrade to famous songs.","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13555684057","text":"Needs to keep up with competition. There are plenty of apps out to learn. This one starts in beginners and jumps around in skill sets while lacking some of the options with the other paid apps","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13543614855","text":"A couple suggestions. First of all love the app… but I thought singing would be cool.. if not also cool.. but if there was a way to download lessons that’d be DOPE","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13499620988","text":"Screen recorded me while not using the app. After installing this I started noticing a red ring around the notch indicating that my phone was screen recording, regardless of running the app. For example, when I went to Messages it would do display the screen recording indicator. \n\nI prefer to avoid applications that I have to be suspicious of. If it was a mistake in how they implemented recording, then I would prefer to avoid using apps that are written poorly. \n\nIt more or less worked. Seemed to be particularly sensitive to out of tune g strings.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13490365433","text":"Great Guitar app. One of the better ones.. I think this is one of the best apps out there for guitar learning. They’re focused on providing quality over quantity. I’ve been on here for a little over 3.5 years now. From beginner to intermediate, I think this app will help you improve. For Advanced players…I’m not sure. When in doubt sign up and try it out. The free 7 day trial, lets you try everything. I still take one on one guitar lessons with a teacher. This app fills the gap. Some will complain that the “device” mic detection has issues…to that I say you need to get an audio interface. Once you get beyond the early basics, the microphone detection isn’t as precise. This has nothing to do with the app…it’s physics! Get an audio interface. They range in price for $30 and up. Just do an internet search for “audio interface”. I highly recommend the UA Volt. They make great products. They are on the pricier end of the devices. \nBack to the app…the developers and content creators are well involved with the community. They recently added a forum section for user and the developers to interface in. The support staff responds quickly. \nAs for as the content, it’s well made. It’s not just a bunch of famous songs just to have them. Again the focus is guitar learning…learning the guitar is something you have to put the time in. So, go ahead and sign up…look from me on the forum in the app if you have questions (Marshall).","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13472403478","text":"Beginning to play and having fun. I played a little as a teenager, but never spent enough time with it. Now just started up again at age 49. Wanted some new hobbies since I own my own business. I got a teacher and started taking lessons. I recently bought a new Gibson Studio Les Paul and tried out the Gibson App. It’s a lot of fun and now im addicted. I’m starting to love playing the Blues Riffs. Highly recommend. Also I paid for the premium + subscription and it’s great. For the depth of this app, it’s a great price. It’s wild seeing the few reviews of people wanting such a great product for free. Nothing good in life is free.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13465378595","text":"I enjoy the Gibson APP. This is a great program to start playing guitar or to improve upon your skills. For me it takes me out of my normal routine of playing the same old stuff and adds structure to my learning. At first the course is very basic but if you stay with it and learn the lessons as presented you will find that you can pick up some new skills and become a more proficient guitarist. I find playing with the APP I have a defined set of goals and standards that keep me focused and on track.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13457080698","text":"Broke People Can’t Use!!. I downloaded it and after the first few lessons they make you pay for everything else. You cannot learn ANYTHING without emptying your pockets!","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13451437152","text":"don’t get it. you basically cannot do anything without paying for it. you get a lesson on ONE string then you can’t go further","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13444643461","text":"Don’t use for tuning. Tuning is super wonky, ended up breaking a string because of it. Didn’t use it as a learning app","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13444064901","text":"Connectivity issues desktop. This app works well 1/16 of the time I try to use it. No matter what native configuration of audio settings I use, the Gibson app will not run often on my desktop due to not recognizing the headphones. Native 1/8 Jack, preamp, like universal audio, or AirPods.  M2 MacBook loaded.  When this app works, it’s amazing.  When it doesn’t, I wish I never spent the money.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13440621036","text":"Great during the trial. It is really cool at first. You think yeah it’s worth it. Then after you buy it unless you read closely you realize all the cool stuff you were learning goes away unless you pay a subscription fee. Seemed expensive to start with the.n to tack on a fee. Just disappointing. I am not one to complain what things cost. This just seemed unfair. Frankly I felt scammed..","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13437230898","text":"Gibson. It’s really good but the tuning needs work","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13427637271","text":"To expensive. This app is very funny easy to learn, but the subscriptions are way too expensive and the only thing I really want is the lessons I don’t care about the other stuff","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13415096311","text":"Live this app!!. The Gibson App exceeded my expectations. The lesson structure is very well thought out and actually helps you improve instead of overwhelming you. I love the daily practice recommendations and the slow-down feature for songs. The production quality of the videos is excellent. If you’re serious about learning guitar, this is one of the best apps you can use.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13402457633","text":"App is crashing. Currently the app is unusable because it crashes when starting a song. I just started a trial and this is not a good sign at all.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13402091762","text":"Completely Unstable. Great app when it works, but unfortunately its completely unstable and crashes anytime you try and do a lesson.  Hopefully they push out an update soon to fix this bug.  Deleting and reinstalling doesn’t work and it crashed on every device I have tried","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13401167340","text":"Crash. I paid $200 for lessons on this app and it crashed every time it tries to listen to how I’m playing.  I’m not that bad am I?  Seriously.  The app crashes before I can even play.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13399576831","text":"Was Doing Well Until….. I got so far along and then the app just force closes on its own. Paid a lot of $$$$$$ for this.","score":2,"date":""},{"id":"13399536869","text":"Crashes constantly. Tried the free trial and after each lesson the app crashes when trying to go the next lesson. I have to go back in each time and restart. Did that for about ten minutes but got too frustrated. That is annoying and enough to make me look at other options before buying paying.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13398895647","text":"App crash. Soon as I start a lesson the app crashes. I’ve went back in 10 times in a row trying to get a lesson going and crashes every time. Frustration is a bad part of trying to learn! I deleted the app and cancel trial after 10 minutes.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13383096427","text":"Hard App to Use. App is not easy to use. App uses phone speaker but it doesn’t often register what you are playing. Furthermore, the app is not fun and hasn’t taught me anything. I have played guitar in the past and wanted to get back i to it. There has to be better options.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13342972431","text":"excellent app. i started a year and a half ago and am already on the advanced courses. this app is incredible. love the scale workouts and all the new guides, please keep them coming. using an irig 2 to wire in to the app, the effects are really nice. bring back metallica and pink floyd though, please!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13330502282","text":"Pricing????. After day 7 how much????","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13254318189","text":"Totally worth it. If you’re a beginner or want to get better at guitar, you’ll benefit from this app a lot! I’d suggest adding the famous songs package. It’s getting much better every day with new guides and songs.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13250797194","text":"Love it!. Great instructors that do an amazing job of breaking down songs into learnable chunks. The gaming version for the tabs is really useful. I think my timing got better ha ha. The Chicago Blues course on this app is a fav!!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13249335856","text":"An actual good learning app. I don’t normally leave reviews but thought I should for this. Huge fan of classic rock and jazz and I’ve had a guitar I’ve wanted to learn to play for 20 years that was more than just a wall ornament. I’ve tried some Udemy classes, I’ve tried books, I’ve tried YouTube but none really stuck. Not a lot of in person teachers where I am either. \n\nI’ve been using this for two weeks now and I can honestly say I’m seeing progress and improvements. When I first started I was hitting around 80-90% of notes and have been progressing normally. Decided to go back and try to beginner lessons and I’m 100%ing all the lesson songs in one shot. That’s after practicing lessons 4-5 times a week and repeating some I struggled with. \n\nIt’s spendy, basic subscription is 20 bucks a month and the popular songs is another 5 (really it’s 25 because the hits add on soft locks you out of a lot of stuff) but it’s cheaper than a teacher and I’m seeing progress. \n\nThe app starts you off on the e string and then adds more and more frets, then the B string and adds more frets, then you add the middle finger, etc.","score":5,"date":""}],"sentiment":{"overallSentiment":"positive","painPoints":[{"issue":"Misleading pricing and hidden upsells - premium content locked behind additional paywalls","frequency":"high","severity":"critical","sampleQuotes":["The premium subscription for 19.99 is misleading when you can't even access the second lesson without being up charged 4.99.","when they say pay extra for the famous songs what they actually mean is that the lower tier is lessons only. You can't even play the songs from the lessons outside on the lesson."]},{"issue":"Poor note detection accuracy, especially on phones","frequency":"medium","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["The picking up of the notes is not that good with a phone. It works sometime and sometimes it doesn't","I didn't even have my guitar in my hands. Showed I hit 45% accuracy and I didn't even have my guitar in my hands."]},{"issue":"Teaching method doesn't work for all learners","frequency":"low","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["after 3 weeks of daily lessons, I'm no better at guitar. I also did not like the 'augmented reality' piece, which involves playing out of key notes in the name of an easier learning curve."]},{"issue":"Limited song library and artist content disappearing","frequency":"low","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["after I renewed my subscription many artists disappeared, Hendrix, nirvana, metalica, Beatles, foo fighters and others.","The website still show some artists that doesn't exist in the library."]},{"issue":"Poor customer service responsiveness","frequency":"low","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["Costumer service doesn't answer, it's is a terrible experience."]},{"issue":"Lack of specific feedback from AI instructor","frequency":"low","severity":"minor","sampleQuotes":["Regardless of 1 star or 3 stars on a lesson, you still get a 'good job!'","maybe some better AI during the lesson to say, 'looks like this string was muted, try this'."]}],"featureRequests":[{"feature":"Friends list and competitive multiplayer features","demand":"high","sampleQuotes":["the only thing I'd like to add is a friends list. I'd like to be able to have friendly competitions with my friends and keep up with each others progress","It could also potentially open the door for mobile play sessions amongst players."]},{"feature":"Recap and review system for previous lessons","demand":"medium","sampleQuotes":["I think there should be a 'recap' each time you login to practice, it should go over what you learned last time"]},{"feature":"Pop quizzes and retention testing","demand":"medium","sampleQuotes":["'pop quizzes' and do random tests to help you retain things"]}],"praisedAspects":["Effective teaching method and curriculum structure","Great value for price compared to in-person lessons","Instant feedback helps identify mistakes quickly","Easy to use and navigate interface","Flexibility to learn at your own pace and on your own time","Backing tracks and rhythm support","Comprehensive song library and learning content","Fun and engaging competitive ranking system","Works great on iPad","Built-in amp feature for iPhone/iPad","Excellent progression tracking and visible improvement","Ability to learn from beginner to advanced levels"],"summary":"Overall sentiment is strongly positive with most users praising Gibson as an effective, engaging, and affordable alternative to in-person guitar lessons. Users love the app's curriculum structure, instant feedback, convenient scheduling, and competitive ranking system. However, significant pain points include misleading pricing with hidden paywalls for premium content, inconsistent note detection accuracy (especially on phones), and poor customer service. Some users report the teaching method doesn't suit all learning styles. Feature requests focus on social features (friends list and multiplayer competitions) and enhanced learning tools (recap systems and pop quizzes). Despite these issues, the app maintains excellent user satisfaction due to its overall effectiveness at accelerating guitar skill development across various proficiency levels."},"score":{"marketSize":14,"dissatisfaction":25,"feasibility":72,"compositeScore":36},"scanId":"fceeb718-5c98-4761-b59a-4f7d7f1fc08b","createdAt":"2026-03-08T15:48:33.983Z","gapAnalysis":null,"blueOcean":null}}

data: {"type":"opportunity","opportunity":{"id":"787913d0-ea5a-4040-a4ab-299ed123b09c","scrapedApp":{"id":"1553283646","title":"memoryOS・Improve Memory Skills","store":"app_store","genre":"6017","score":0,"ratings":0,"reviewCount":50,"installs":"N/A","description":"memoryOS contains interactive bite-sized lessons by a 2X World Memory Champion and an educational 3D game of Virtual Mind Palaces - all in one easy-to-use app. It utilizes scientifically proven memory techniques, spaced repetition and patented game mechanics to enhance long-term memory storage and improve knowledge retention.\n\nmemoryOS is loved by 500,000+ people worldwide because it is a whole new, joyful & game-changing tool for obtaining the most effective memorization skills.\n\nCo-founded by Jonas von Essen, who went from struggling to remember to becoming a World Memory Champion, winning on Who Wants To Be a Millionaire, \"Jeopardy, and setting a world record by memorizing 100,000 decimals of Pi . \n\nmemoryOS app has over 18k public worldwide ratings on Apple and Google app stores combined, averaging 4.8 stars. Users also continue adding 5-star reviews daily, sharing how effective and life-changing memoryOS has been for them. Also, memoryOS remains the most crowdfunded app in Kickstarter’s history.\n\nMemorization is as important as reading and writing and should be taught as our base skill. Our mission is to enable millions of people to remember needed information easily.\n\nWith memoryOS, you will learn how to memorize:\n\n- Names, Long speeches, Lists of items, Birthdays, Personal facts, Passwords, Trivia, Languages, Vocabulary and phrases, Countries and Capitals, Flags, Historical timeline, Numbers, Periodic table\n- Content of complete books, Dates of significant events, Complex data structures, Concepts, and figures\n- Art, Anatomy, Decks of cards, Advanced number systems; Long sequences of numbers, Binary Digits\n\nYou will also learn:\n\n- How to keep track of years, months, weeks, and days \n- Advanced study techniques, Spaced Repetition system, Speed memorization\n\n\nWhy did Google Brands Accelerator recognize memoryOS as being 'Light Years Ahead' in the memory space?\n\n• memoryOS delivers results:\n\nDuring our pre-launch phase, thousands of users completed our demo and, on average, had a 70% increase in recall and a 60% increase in recall speed just after the first ~40min session.\n\n• Providing your mind with structured storage space:\n\nWe have spent tens of thousands of hours creating and optimizing our Virtual Mind Palaces, so you don’t have to spend months constructing your own the hard way. These virtual palaces serve as blueprints for your mind's storage space, allowing you to easily encode, store and recall like a memory champion.\n\n• A proven innovative approach that works:\n\nDuring our research and development stage, thousands of people of all age groups and even those with difficult medical conditions found memoryOS as an effective and useful tool. Actual results exceeded our team’s expectations.\n\n• Gamified edtech at its best:\n\nmemoryOS has proven to work on people with no prior gaming experience - anyone can use it. Utilizing the power of the Unity game engine, memoryOS is widely accessible on all mobile and tablet devices and is soon coming to VR.\n\n--\n\nJoining memoryOS is free. This provides extensive value on the free plan, and you are not obligated to pay to start using it. You can subscribe to a Student Premium plan for as low as $3.49/month when billed annually or $4.99/month when billed monthly (it can be 10-20% higher in some countries due to local taxes). You can subscribe through the 'Shop' section of the memoryOS app and find the above-mentioned or go to your App Store app's profile and choose a desired plan there. Recurring payments will automatically renew unless you cancel your account at least 24 hours before the end of the current subscription period. You can manage your subscription, cancel anytime, or turn off auto-renewal by accessing your iTunes account.\n\nJoin the memoryOS community of over 500,000+ early adopters who share this memorable journey!\n\n--\n\nTerms: memoryOS.com/terms\nPrivacy policy: memoryOS.com/privacy-policy\n\nLearn more at: memoryOS.com\n\nContact us: support@memoryOS.com","icon":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Purple221/v4/5c/7f/23/5c7f23ad-4c6f-edfa-8c0a-9face04de1f4/AppIcon-0-0-1x_U007emarketing-0-8-0-85-220.png/100x100bb.png","url":"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/memoryos-improve-memory-skills/id1553283646?uo=2","developer":"Encoder Inc.","isEstimatedInstalls":false},"reviews":[{"id":"13822177021","text":"Fun learning great skills. Building lots of skills that will be useful for life.  Good to strengthen my recall ability by linking  things to memorized structures, and abstract things made concrete and memorable.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13821102487","text":"Memory improvement. I am finding this app a really well designed program. I could never learned this from a book. Work thats fun!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13820233714","text":"Deceitful offers. Don’t be tricked, they’ll charge 6$ for the “one month offer”, i just bought it yesterday, and when i was checking today inside, they had the settings that on march 11th will charge “the expert” plan 149$ !!! Ran!!!","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13818954987","text":"Cool Mind game. This is amazing.Help your brain focus and concentrate.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13818555316","text":"For coins but also honest. I am seriously loving the ways to memorise things. And if I’m being honest I’m enjoying it. It takes a while but it’s like playing games hahaha.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13815811193","text":"Would have been a good app without the paganism. I like the idea of this app and function. It uses the memory palace technique which works really well but I canceled it bc one of the first rooms is called the “Druid Space” and the objects you have to remember are a Druid staff with an animal skull and crystals, a stone table, magic herbs and a sickle. I’m not into paganism and spells so this app wasn’t for me\n\nEDIT: They sent a nice response explaining that they chose those objects bc they are memorable not bc of religious preference…but none-the-less, those are religious items that go against my beliefs so I don’t feel comfortable using the app and just thought people should know before they spend the money.","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13814589345","text":"Life changing. I don’t have a great memory and I usually don’t do very well at any type of trivia nights. This could be a game changer.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13810870242","text":"So cool!. I’ve just started, but the tools are immediately useful.  There is no app like it.  It’s fun, interesting and incredibly useful- love it","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13806667831","text":"More than I even hoped for!. I hoped I could find an app that would really help me with my faulty memory after near death experience from a TBI. But it seems like all apps went to charge you something every month in order to use them. And then they want me to cancel it if I don’t like it well, since my problem is a faulty memory I don’t remember to go cancel them. This one teaches you with excellent information, ideas, tips, and tricks that actually work and then builds up on them as you go through the course. It is fantastic, and yes, you can pay for more later, but the free version is phenomenal and when it comes time to pay, I’ll do it because it’s more than proven it’s effectiveness and worth!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13804559617","text":"It interesting. Just started so can’t really say but it’s been interesting.","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13801265614","text":"Fantastic!. Such an interesting look into how the mind retains information! This app offers a fun and easy way to strengthen memorization through association lessons.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13800732184","text":"Fun!. This is a fun way to challenge your memory. I’m learning several tips to help me remember lists and become a better speaker without notes. The room graphics are excellent!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13799021020","text":"My thoughts. Positive sentiments for this app. For those who struggle with creating and imbedding memory palaces,this offers an easy simple way to alleviate that struggle.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13790061932","text":"Quality. By far one of the best learning apps for teens. Reminds me so much of prodigy. Best app to keep u intrigued while learning.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13789286916","text":"Great app!. Quick and simple lessons (not to be confused with easy. Lol)","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13786147025","text":"Memory. Great","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13786094601","text":"Too much $. Not bad but expensive, always wanting more $","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13785626476","text":"Makes memorizing easy. So far, I’m enjoying the memory exercises. The graphics are entertaining and the information is presented in a non threatening manner.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13785069890","text":"It’s a good app. I was skeptical at first, because some of the methods are a little goofy, but it genuinely does make remembering things much easier.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13784324105","text":"Amazing memory info.. Very enjoyable way to unlock untapped resources to improve your memory.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13782566336","text":"Memory OS. Excellent program!!!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13782230590","text":"great game!. this game is so cool and fun","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13782002827","text":"Fun to improve. Very clever way to enjoy improving memory.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13781371196","text":"Incredible App. Let me start by saying I always thought of myself as having the worst memory of anyone I’ve ever met. And that’s not just me being harsh on myself; other people have commented on how bad my memory is. I have ADHD, which impacts my working memory. However, I also have a very poor long term memory as well and can’t remember vacations, movies, navigation, things I’ve learned, etc. to the point where it’s had a significant impact on my daily functioning and relationships.\n\nI’ve learned about neuroplasticity a bit so I figured I may as well try to train my memory. I’ve been doing the lessons in the app using the methods, and to my shock, I’ve been getting through each lesson and mind palace with near 100% accuracy. This app has already shown me that I can use tricks and intentionality to have great short term memory. My hope is that these skills end up improving my long term memory as well with practice. For the first time in a long time I have hope and belief that my memory can actually improve, instead of feeling like it’s always getting worse. This is especially true in the age of over reliance on AI and technology in place of memory.\n\nThe app is well designed and the instructor is really good at explaining concepts. I like the streaks system as it keeps you accountable to practicing every day. I wish I knew about these techniques when I was in school as it would’ve been SO helpful when studying. I may end up purchasing a subscription in the future, but I am so grateful for how much content you can access for free. It’s way more than most apps would give you. This app is a must have for anyone who wants to improve their memory!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13779345012","text":"Definitely worth a try. I definitely see a difference.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13779056493","text":"Fun and intuitive experience!. I’ve been using the app for only a day, and can already see how fun and intuitive this experience will be. Great work!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13776912904","text":"Early thoughts. Too early to give a full and honest review. I am still a bit confused by the app. Initially there had been word remembrance lessons and now I seem to be searching rooms, remembering items and I can’t figure out how to get back to the word lessons. So for the moment it is going to take some further exploration to understand the possible benefits of this app. That being said it seems promising.","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13775655683","text":"Fun and interesting. This memory application is similar to a game. I used to play as a child.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13771367374","text":"Buyer beware. This app might help your memory and it might be fun and engaging but they do not provide any warning when you subscription is up for renewal. You have to jump through hoops to get a refund. I will leave this review on here until they change their policy and send out reminder emails to their subscribers when subscription charges will be billed.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13770481144","text":"Fun!. So far so good! Really like the app. So much fun!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13770465127","text":"CDC. I think this app will be challenging but doable. Hopefully I’ve gotten the challenges down. I’m excited there may be some help after all. ❤️","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13770451599","text":"Not satisfying. Very difficult to do","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13770337358","text":"Scam. Doubled my subscription and won’t give me my money back. Tech support ignores my attempts to. Scam","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13769725434","text":"Pretty cool. I’m actually surprised at how well you can actually remember things while applying the techniques.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13769467299","text":"Super Memory. I’m a whizz","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13769455300","text":"It works. I started going through the lessons and realized how well it works. It even become fun to learn and try to remember list of things. I’m using the free version but will probably switch to the pay as it’s totally worth it. I was so bad at memorizing stuff and names that it took me 6months to remember the name of my first girlfriend. I started remembering her name the day we split up :) (true story).","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13768286818","text":"Room 1. Fun","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13766888057","text":"Good So Far. Just started and they want a review right away. I like it and I need the coins, so…","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13764281245","text":"No Support. App would get to one page asking to match images but would not load images. I received only an automated reply saying they were busy when I reported the problem but no follow up.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13764223527","text":"Good, but…. The game of memorizing palaces using visual cues works for the majority of people but is less useful for those of us with no mind’s eye. I memorize through patterns and words. It would be really good to see if this could be accommodated in your app.","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13763659675","text":"Look out. Pricing isn’t transparent.. Just two days in and it’s already locked – can’t move forward unless I give them more money than I already have.  I wouldn’t mind so much if they’d been transparent about pricing in the beginning.","score":4,"date":""},{"id":"13759988474","text":"Love this app!. I have gotten great value from using this.  It’s helping so many areas of my life as I use my mind palace more each day.  I love visualizing and sorting things and this skill is helping my business, flow, and order of my day too!  So cool","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13758658015","text":"Marginal improvement. Not only gains after 1 week","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13756350394","text":"Great Program. I am very impressed with this app. It is so easy to follow and the results of improved memory is almost immediate.","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13754525134","text":"It costs!. I went to the comments to see what it costs. It’s  $5 a month. I wish someone had said.","score":1,"date":""},{"id":"13752912486","text":"Impressive!. I am very impressed with the strategies and methods used to awaken my sleeping memory power.  \nThank you!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13750325292","text":"Memoryos. This is the best game I ever played\nMovies fo do lalafo","score":3,"date":""},{"id":"13750222719","text":"Excelente. Divertido","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13749123255","text":"Fantastic. Just starting but it keeps you on your toes. Really enjoy the learning!","score":5,"date":""},{"id":"13747995091","text":"No notice before being charged. I’m upset I was not reminded before my card was charged upon renewal. No possibility of refund. I know this is standard practice but it is shady and it’s insane that we accept it. \n\nI tried the app and don’t like it. The training is disorganized and the time commitment needed to use it effectively is much more than advertised.","score":1,"date":""}],"sentiment":{"overallSentiment":"positive","painPoints":[{"issue":"Deceptive pricing and hidden subscription charges","frequency":"low","severity":"critical","sampleQuotes":["Don't be tricked, they'll charge 6$ for the \"one month offer\", i just bought it yesterday, and when i was checking today inside, they had the settings that on march 11th will charge \"the expert\" plan 149$ !!!","Not bad but expensive, always wanting more $"]},{"issue":"High cost and aggressive monetization","frequency":"medium","severity":"major","sampleQuotes":["Too much $.","But it seems like all apps went to charge you something every month in order to use them."]}],"featureRequests":[],"praisedAspects":["Effective memory improvement techniques and methods","Well-designed and engaging learning experience","Fun and entertaining approach to learning","Helpful graphics and visual aids","Useful practical skills for everyday life","Strong free version content","Clear, easy-to-follow lessons","Addresses memory palace creation effectively"],"summary":"memoryOS receives overwhelmingly positive sentiment with the vast majority of users (18 out of 22 reviews) giving 5-star ratings. Users consistently praise the app's innovative teaching methods, engaging interface, and genuine effectiveness at improving memory skills through association and memory palace techniques. However, a critical concern emerges around deceptive pricing practices and aggressive monetization strategy, particularly the hidden automatic subscription charges that convert from discounted monthly offers to expensive annual plans without clear user awareness. While most users acknowledge the app provides excellent value in its free tier, the pricing transparency issue and overall cost represent the primary friction points that could undermine otherwise exceptional user satisfaction."},"score":{"marketSize":14,"dissatisfaction":25,"feasibility":72,"compositeScore":36},"scanId":"fceeb718-5c98-4761-b59a-4f7d7f1fc08b","createdAt":"2026-03-08T15:48:34.227Z","gapAnalysis":null,"blueOcean":null}}

